Some of Mzansi’s favourite Gospel music heavyweights will perform at the inaugural Gospel Emonti music festival during this year’s festive season. The festival, due to take place on 23 December 2018 in East London will feature Pastor Benjamin Dube, Dr Tumi, Lebo Sekgobela, Betusile, Dumi Mkokstad and Veliswa Skeyi. Gospel Emonti will be hosted by Umhlobo Wenene’s Nomthunzi Vuza aka Mama Ka Ma-Asi and Amaza Ntshanga. The one-day Gospel spectacle will start at 10:00 on Sunday, 23 December at Buffalo City Stadium in East London. Tickets are already available from Computicket and will cost R350 and above. 